Package: vigiar
Type: Package
Title: Download and Process VIGIAR Environmental Health Surveillance Data
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Ryan",
           family = "Santos",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "ryan.paulo@gsuite.iff.edu.br",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-6770-2001")))
Author: Ryan Santos
Maintainer: Ryan Santos <ryan.paulo@gsuite.iff.edu.br>
Description: Provides a programmatic interface to download, process,
    and explore the complete dataset from Brazil's VIGIAR (Vigilancia
    em Saude Ambiental) public Power BI dashboard, maintained by the
    Brazilian Ministry of Health. Follows the microdatasus architecture
    with separate download and processing layers plus exploratory
    visualisation. Includes: Power BI anonymous session management,
    DSR (Data Shape Response) decompression, column standardisation,
    IBGE code validation, typed S3 tibbles with metadata, a complete
    variable dictionary, descriptive time series, choropleth maps via
    geobr, and export to CSV/RDS/Parquet. Data covers PM2.5 air quality,
    population exposure, health indicators, attributable fractions,
    and indoor solid fuel exposure. Package architecture inspired by
    microdatasus (Saldanha et al.). Built on httr2, dplyr, and tibble.
